{
  "text": "In the present study, we therefore compared capture by an irrelevant color distractor during color search under conditions of either certainty or uncertainty about the distractor color, and we measured eye movements to ensure that any RT interference was based on oculomotor capture and not on nonspatial filtering costs alone. There is a tight coupling between eye movements and attention (e.g., [CITATION_1] . If irrelevant color distractors of a known certain color can capture attention during search for color targets, participants should more frequently fixate the irrelevant distractors than any nonsingleton distractor.",
